#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:146
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:154
msgid "Welcome to Wesnoth!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:148
msgid ""
"For this tutorial, you are playing Konrad. You are standing on the keep, and "
"your mentor Delfador is on the east side of the river. You can move the "
"mouse over a unit to see a summary of its abilities and stats on the right "
"of the screen."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:156
msgid ""
"For this tutorial, you are playing Li’sar. You are standing on the keep, and "
"your mentor Delfador is on the east side of the river. you can move the "
"mouse over a unit to see a summary of its abilities and stats on the right "
"of the screen."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:162
msgid "Click on Konrad"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:164
msgid "Click on Li’sar"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:198
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:206
msgid "Movement"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:200
msgid ""
"When you select a unit, in this case Konrad, the places he can move to are "
"highlighted. All units have a certain number of <i>movement points</i>, "
"which dictate how many hexes that unit can move per turn. Normally, moving "
"one hex uses one movement point, but moving across different types of hexes, "
"or <i>terrains</i>, can use up more. You will learn more about that later. "
"To move, simply click on your destination. You can press <b>u</b> to undo a "
"move if you move to the wrong place."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:208
msgid ""
"When you select a unit, in this case Li’sar, the places she can move to are "
"highlighted. All units have a certain number of <i>movement points</i>, "
"which dictate how many hexes that unit can move per turn. Normally, moving "
"one hex uses one movement point, but moving across different types of hexes, "
"or <i>terrains</i>, can use up more. You will learn more about that later. "
"To move, simply click on your destination. You can press <b>u</b> to undo a "
"move if you move to the wrong place."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:214
msgid "Move Konrad next to Delfador."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:216
msgid "Move Li’sar next to Delfador."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:233
msgid "Good morning, Delfador! Is it time to attack things?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:238
msgid "Um, well..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:243
msgid "Have you found an orc for me to fight, huh? A troll?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:248
msgid "Quiet! I will summon an enemy for you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:295
msgid "... this quintain!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:300
msgid "A quintain? You want me to fight a dummy?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:306
msgid ""
"You have $student_hp hitpoints and a sword, boy. I’m fairly sure you’ll win."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:311
msgid ""
"female^Young lady, you have $student_hp hitpoints and a sword. I’m fairly "
"sure you’ll win."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:319
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:326
msgid "Attacking"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:321
msgid ""
"To attack the quintain, first select the attacker (Konrad) then the target "
"(the quintain). You will see an attack description. When you click <b>OK</"
"b>, Konrad will attack."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:328
msgid ""
"To attack the quintain, first select the attacker (Li’sar) then the target "
"(the quintain). You will see an attack description. When you click <b>OK</"
"b>, Li’sar will attack."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:343
msgid "Hey! This quintain fights back!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:348
msgid "Hmm, perhaps we should have started with a doll."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:353
msgid "Should I retreat?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:358
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:656
msgid "Good idea!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:364
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:371
msgid "Crowns"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:366
msgid ""
"The tiny golden crown above your leader (Konrad) indicates he is a side "
"leader. In most scenarios, you will lose if your leader is killed. Be sure "
"to keep him safe!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:373
msgid ""
"The tiny golden crown above your leader (Li’sar) indicates she is a side "
"leader. In most scenarios, you will lose if your leader is killed. Be sure "
"to keep her safe!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:383
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, you’ve used up your turn attacking the quintain. The quintain "
"now gets to attack."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:388
msgid "The <i>dummy</i> gets a turn?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:393
msgid ""
"Yes. It’s a magical quintain! It gets 5 chances to hit you for 3 damage "
"each. If it hits every time, you’ll drop from $student_hp to "
"$($student_hp-15) hitpoints. Brace yourself!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:400
msgid "Turns"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:402
msgid ""
"Every turn, each side in a scenario gets a chance to make their move. Once "
"you’ve completed everything you wish to do this turn, click on the <b>End "
"Turn</b> button in the bottom right of the screen. The other teams, whether "
"controlled by the AI or other human players, will then make their move. Some "
"scenarios must be completed in a certain number of turns. You can see what "
"turn it is, and any applicable turn limit, next to the flag icon at the top "
"of the screen."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#. [event]: (id=Delfador) 14 8}, (id=Delfador) facing nw}
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:405
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:451
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:536
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:331
msgid "End your turn"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:420
msgid "Ouch! I need to heal! Only $student_hp hitpoints left!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:425
msgid ""
"There is a village on the other side of the river. Visiting villages is a "
"good idea, and ending your turn in one will heal you. To the village!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:429
msgid "Move Konrad to the nearest village"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:431
msgid "Move Li’sar to the nearest village"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:444
msgid "Villages"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:446
msgid ""
"You have captured a village! It now flies your colors and has been added to "
"your total village count (the house icon at the top of the screen shows how "
"many villages you currently control). Villages provide the gold needed to "
"recruit units. Each turn, you gain two gold plus one for every village you "
"own."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:466
msgid ""
"Since you started your turn on a village, you regained some health! Villages "
"heal units 8 hitpoints per turn, or enough to top off their health, "
"whichever is less. In your case, you regained $student_hp_heal_amount "
"hitpoints."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:471
msgid "Now, it’s time to summon some help against that quintain."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:476
msgid "I’ll recruit some elves!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:481
msgid ""
"A splendid idea! It’s probably best not to attempt attacking the quintain "
"this turn. Instead, you could return to the keep and recruit two units; you "
"have plenty of gold for that."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:485
msgid "Move Konrad to the keep"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:487
msgid "Move Li’sar to the keep"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:505
msgid "Recruiting"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:507
msgid ""
"Whenever you’re on a <i>keep</i>, you can <i>recruit</i> units on the castle "
"tiles around it by right-clicking and selecting <b>Recruit</b>. Note that "
"newly recruited units cannot act the turn you recruit them; you will be able "
"to use them next turn. This scenario you have only one type of unit to "
"choose from: the Elvish Fighter."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:510
msgid "Recruit two Elvish Fighters"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:529
msgid "Traits"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:531
msgid ""
"Be sure to examine the <i>traits</i> of your new recruits. They are listed "
"under its race in the sidebar. Traits can subtly affect how you use your "
"troops. For example, units with the <i>quick</i> trait can move a extra hex "
"each turn, or units with the <i>intelligent</i> trait require 20% less "
"experience to level up. A full list of all possible traits may be found in "
"help."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:557
msgid ""
"Hey, the quintain just healed 2 hitpoints! I’d better attack it at once!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:562
msgid "Yes, if a unit doesn’t do anything for a turn, it will slowly heal."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:567
msgid ""
"Before you send your fighters against the quintain, you should know they "
"have two kinds of attack..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:572
msgid "I’ll tell them to use the one that does the most damage!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:577
msgid ""
"And which would that be? The sword (5–4) or the bow (3–3)? I suppose you’ll "
"find out..."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:580
msgid "Attack the quintain with your fighters"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:598
msgid ""
"You wouldn’t do anything stupid like charging that quintain yourself again, "
"now would you? Use the fighters you recruited first; they’ll be a lot of "
"help."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:627
msgid ""
"Your elf used a sword (5–4; or 5 damage, 4 attacks), which is a <i>melee</i> "
"attack. The quintain defended with its melee attack (3–5). The ranged attack "
"(the bow) would have been safer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:639
msgid ""
"Your elf used a bow, which is a <i>ranged</i> attack (3–3; or 3 damage, 3 "
"attacks). The quintain has no ranged attack, only a melee attack, so it "
"could not defend itself."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:654
msgid "Keep attacking with both elves until the quintain is finished!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:669
msgid "Maybe you should recruit another elf?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:679
msgid "Unit Descriptions"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:681
msgid ""
"You can right click on a unit to see a detailed <b>Unit Description</b>."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:691
msgid "Protect Your Troops"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:693
msgid ""
"Remember to pull back wounded units into villages and recruit more if "
"needed. Take special care of units with the highest <i>experience points "
"(XP)</i> so they can gain levels and become more powerful."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:703
msgid "Support"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:705
msgid ""
"Each village you control will <i>support</i> one unit for free. After that, "
"each unit costs you one gold per turn."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:715
msgid "You had really better finish off that quintain."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:725
msgid "Advancement"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:727
msgid ""
"When a unit gains enough experience points (the <i>experience bar</i>, if "
"present, is on the <b>right</b> of the <i>hitpoints bar</i>), it will gain a "
"level. Elvish Fighters have two advancement options, and you will be able to "
"choose which one you want. However, second level units cost twice as much to "
"support as first level units."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:737
msgid "Defenses"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:740
msgid ""
"Whenever one of your units is selected, you’ll see varying percentages as "
"you move the mouse over the map. The higher the percentage, the more "
"<i>defense</i> that unit has in that kind of terrain. For example, most "
"units have good defenses in castles and villages but poor defenses in "
"rivers. However, these quintains use a <i>magical</i> attack, which always "
"has a 70% chance of hitting no matter what terrain its target occupies."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:752
msgid "Agh! This training is too much for me..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:779
msgid "The quintain is destroyed, and I have gained more experience!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:784
msgid ""
"Yes, you gain experience through battle, especially by killing an opponent. "
"Gain enough experience and you’ll become more powerful."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:790
msgid ""
"Now, Konrad, I will leave you with more dummies to practice on! After that, "
"we have real work to do..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:795
msgid ""
"Now, Li’sar, I will leave you with more dummies to practice on! After that, "
"we have real work to do..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:869
msgid "Note"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:871
msgid ""
"These dummies only attack if you are a single tile away. With care, you "
"should be able to kill them one at a time."
msgstr ""

#. [set_menu_item]: id=skip_item
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:879
msgid "End Scenario"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:894
msgid ""
"Do you want to keep practicing? You can end this scenario at any time by "
"using the <b>End Scenario</b> item in the context menu to move on to the "
"next phase of your training."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:896
msgid "Yes, I’m still figuring it out."
msgstr ""

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:899
msgid "No, I think I’ve got it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:918
msgid ""
"Well, I think I know the basics. Onwards! Maybe I can fight in a real battle "
"next?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:934
msgid "Victory"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:936
msgid ""
"After your victory notice, the map will be grayed out to indicate that the "
"scenario is over; this is called <i>linger mode</i>. You will still be able "
"to examine the final positions and state of your troops and any surviving "
"enemies. When you’re finished, click the <b>End Scenario</b> button to go on "
"to the next scenario in the campaign."
msgstr ""

